The UV–visible and fluorescence intensity (PL) spectra of the synthesized BGQDs at 1000μg/mL in aqueous solution are shown in Fig. 3
                     (a) and (b), respectively. One broad absorption peak was observed at 320nm, which may be attributed to a π–π* transition and entrapping of the excited state energy by the surface states, causing strong emission [30]. A broad emission peak at 445nm, which is the emission wavelength range of blue light, was observed when the BGQD solution was excited at 360nm (Fig. 3(b)). The BGQD solution emitted strong blue PL with approximately 24% quantum yield under a UV lamp at 365nm (Fig. 1(a) and Table 1
                     ).
